Class ScannerConfig.OcrParams

    public class ScannerConfig.OcrParams
extends java.lang.Object
    The OcrParams class provides access to OCR parameters that are available to configure.

    • Field Detail

      • inverseOcr

        public ScannerConfig.InverseOcr inverseOcr
        Setting to change the OCR behavior for white or light words on a black or dark background. 

         
 	Example Usage:
 	ocrParams.inverseOcr = InverseOcr.REGULAR_ONLY;

      • ocrLines

        public ScannerConfig.OcrLines ocrLines
        Number of OCR lines to decode. Some OCR Variants like Visas, TD1, or TD2 ID cards automatically sets the appropriate OCR Lines. 

         
 	Example Usage:
 	ocrParams.ocrLines = OcrLines.ONE_LINE;

      • maxCharacters

        public int maxCharacters
        Maximum number of OCR characters (including spaces) per line to decode. Strings of OCR characters greater than the maximum are ignored. 

         
 	Example Usage:
 	ocrParams.maxCharacters = 100;

      • minCharacters

        public int minCharacters
        Minimum number of OCR characters (not including spaces) per line to decode. Strings of OCR characters less than the minimum are ignored. 

         
 	Example Usage:
 	ocrParams.minCharacters = 3;

      • quietZone

        public int quietZone
        Setting to change the quiet zone to be considered in OCR capturing. 

         
 	Example Usage:
 	ocrParams.quietZone = 50;

      • template

        public java.lang.String template
        Setting to change the template to be used in OCR capturing. Templates are used to precisely matching scanned OCR characters to a desired input format. Carefully constructing an OCR template eliminates scanning errors. 

         
 	Example Usage:
 	ocrParams.template = "54R";

      • orientation

        public ScannerConfig.OcrOrientation orientation
        Specify the orientation of an OCR String to be read 

         
 	Example Usage:
 	ocrParams.orientation = OcrOrientation.DEGREE_90;

      • subset

        public java.lang.String subset
        A custom group of characters in place of a preset font variant 

         
 	Example Usage:
 	ocrParams.subset = "0123456789"; //supports numbers only

      • checkDigitModulus

        public int checkDigitModulus
        Set the check digit modulus value for OCR Check Digit Calculation 

         
 	Example Usage:
 	ocrParams.checkDigitModulus = 1;

      • checkDigitMultiplier

        public java.lang.String checkDigitMultiplier
        Set OCR check digit multipliers for the character positions 

         
 	Example Usage:
 	ocrParams.checkDigitMultiplier = "121212121212";

      • checkDigitValidation

        public ScannerConfig.OcrCheckDigitValidation checkDigitValidation
        Select check digit validation Scheme 

         
 	Example Usage:
 	ocrParams.checkDigitValidation = OcrCheckDigitValidation.NONE;
